<br><p align="justify"></p></h3></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#A6D1FF"><h3>22. 11. <br>St. Cecilia, virgin & martyr
<br><p align="justify">The patroness of music and musicians, was a second or third-century Roman Christian martyr. According to tradition she refused to worship the Roman gods and was beheaded. Her association with music, and the representations of her playing the organ probably grew from a misunderstanding of a fifth-century account of her life.</p></h3></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#A6D1FF"><h3>23. 11. <br>St. Columban, abbot
